# Line-ending policy. This repo is developed on Linux (LF). The GitHub Windows
# runners check out with core.autocrlf=true, which would rewrite tracked bytes
# to CRLF on Windows. For files whose EXACT bytes we depend on, that rewrite is
# a bug, so pin them to LF on every platform.
#
# Most critically: `device_templates.json` is embedded via include_str! and its
# SHA-256 is pinned and asserted on BOTH the Rust and Kotlin sides (#47). A CRLF
# checkout changes those bytes, so the checksum test fails on Windows only (as it
# did in CI). Forcing LF keeps the embedded bytes, and therefore the cross-repo
# hash, identical everywhere. The interop golden vector and the other embedded
# JSON corpora are pinned for the same byte-stability reason.
*.json text eol=lf

# JSON Lines fixtures/journals share the same requirement.
*.jsonl text eol=lf
